Description: Computes genetic offset and the Required Evolutionary Rate
    (REvoRate) from a fitted Gradient Forest model and successive future
    climate raster stacks, as introduced in Morando-Milà et al. (2025)
    <doi:10.1111/eva.XXXXX> "Re-interpreting genetic offset: quantifying
    the least required evolutionary rate under climate change at the
    Mediterranean range margin of European beech" (Evolutionary
    Applications). REvoRate (dG/dt) is derived as the product of the
    rate of genomic change per unit of environmental change (dG/dE) and
    the velocity of environmental change over time (dE/dt), discretised
    over user-defined bidecadal periods. The package also computes plain
    and GF-importance-weighted climate mismatch, extracts all metrics at
    user-supplied site coordinates, and returns tidy wide and long data
    frames ready for analysis and publication-quality plotting.
